lua-rapidjson: Development Branch
===

lua-rapidjson is a rapidjson (https://github.com/Tencent/rapidjson) binding for
Lua 5.1, 5.2, 5.3, and 5.4 with the intention of being pseudo-ABI compatible
with dkjson (https://github.com/LuaDist/dkjson).

API:
  See: src/lua_rapidjsonlib.h (WIP)

Building:
  Generate:
    cmake -H. -Bbuild -G<generator-name>
  Non-standard install location:
    LUA_DIR=.../application/lua cmake -H. -Bbuild -G<generator-name>
  Lua work area:
    LUA_INCLUDE_DIR=.../lua-5.4.0/ cmake -H. -Bbuild -G<generator-name>

  CMake Options:
    LUA_RAPIDJSON_BIT32: Build a -m32 module.
    LUA_RAPIDJSON_DEBUG: Include <ltests.h> from LUA_INCLUDE_DIR
    LUA_RAPIDJSON_EXPLICIT: Throw a lua_Error when handling a non-zero
      rapidjson::ParseErrorCode instead of the default
      <nil, offset, error message> tuple.

  Additional Preprocessor Options:
    LUA_RAPIDJSON_UNSAFE: Disable all _checkstack calls.
    LUA_RAPIDJSON_SANITIZE_KEYS: Throw an error if a __jsonorder key is neither
      a string or numeric; otherwise ignore the key.

Testing:
  Test lua-rapidjson over the rapidjson testing corpus
    lua test/spec/json_load_spec.lua

  To compare speed of rapidjson and other json libraries (include them in source
  directory:
    lua performance/run.lua

Sources & Acknowledgments:
  rapidjson: https://github.com/Tencent/rapidjson
  lua-cmsgpack: https://github.com/xpol/lua-rapidjson
  dkjson: https://github.com/LuaDist/dkjson and its documentation:
    http://dkolf.de/src/dkjson-lua.fsl/wiki?name=Documentation

